{"symbol": "DNAJC2", "uniprot": "Q99543", "protein_name": "DnaJ homolog subfamily C member 2", "length": 621, "function": "Acts both as a chaperone in the cytosol and as a chromatin regulator in the nucleus. When cytosolic, acts as a molecular chaperone: component of the ribosome-associated complex (RAC), a complex involved in folding or maintaining nascent polypeptides in a folding-competent state. In the RAC complex, stimulates the ATPase activity of the ribosome-associated pool of Hsp70-type chaperones HSPA14 that bind to the nascent polypeptide chain. When nuclear, mediates the switching from polycomb-repressed genes to an active state: specifically recruited at histone H2A ubiquitinated at 'Lys-119' (H2AK119ub), and promotes the displacement of the polycomb PRC1 complex from chromatin, thereby facilitating transcription activation", "ensembl_gene": "ENSG00000105821", "scores": {"selectivity": 0.2231, "protein_drug": 0.383, "rna_drug": 0.759}, "flags": {"surface": false, "enzyme": true, "mod_aso": true, "mod_sirna": false}, "details": {"nominated_modality": "ASO", "winning_axis": "RNA", "quadrant": "Both viable", "best_route": "small molecule", "sm_score": "0.468", "sirna_score": "0.246", "aso_score": "0.663"}, "modality": "ASO", "structure": "data/structures/DNAJC2.pdb", "pockets": [{"rank": 1, "druggability": 0.497, "volume": 563.0, "residues": [462, 463, 466, 467, 476, 477, 503, 504, 506, 507, 514, 515, 517, 518]}, {"rank": 2, "druggability": 0.114, "volume": 471.0, "residues": [218, 219, 220, 221, 223, 225, 227, 259, 262, 263, 266, 267, 270]}, {"rank": 3, "druggability": 0.054, "volume": 878.1, "residues": [84, 85, 147, 152, 153, 156, 226, 228, 229, 231, 233, 234, 235, 236, 248, 251, 255]}], "links": [{"key": "uniprot", "label": "UniProt", "url": "https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb/Q99543"}, {"key": "alphafold", "label": "AlphaFold", "url": "https://alphafold.ebi.ac.uk/entry/Q99543"}, {"key": "opentargets", "label": "Open Targets", "url": "https://platform.op